A brave cleric will DA and run thru the firewall, run along the western wall of the temple (NOT over the top - that's a good way to get a DT) and get HT'd by many, many amys. The DA will absorb the HTs, and he/she will run out of the firewall towards the tent bridge, looking back to see how many are on him/her. If there are more than six, cleric will run under the tent bridge, which should get some of the amys stuck in a pathing bug which will cause them to disappear back into the temple for a short time. The cleric should run around and around the hill on which the portal is seated, and the picker should attempt to pick a few amys off him/her. If picker gets more than 4 amys, he/she should run them under the bridge to split them up. if he/she STILL has too many, he/she should kite them around the NW area while the puller attempts to pick off him/her or the cleric. Be careful while kiting, because the Amy knights can cast clinging darkness, which will slow you up and get you wacked. Eventually, SOMEONE will get 1 or 2 amys on them. These can be brought back to camp to be slain, then the process will repeat. Once all the amys being kited have been slain, cleric should DA again again and run up to the firewall, then around to the north and out by the west side of the SS. When he does this, some of the mobs that got peeled off on the bridge will teleport on top of him/her. He/she will kite these around the portal and picker and puller will repeat the earlier process until all the mobs in the temple have been slain. Once this is done, the entire zone will be clear, unless CT is up. If CT is up, everyone should will then run to the SS and buff up for him, then send the sacrificial druid in when he wanders to the NW area of the NE corner of the zone. After the druid gets the finger, charge CT and bring him down. Congratulations! You have cleared the Plane of Fear.<br>
