<br>
FD pulling is not the best method to pull if Cazic is not up, and will certianly get everyone killed if he is.  <br>
<br>
When Cazic is up, a FD has a good chance of working, but often the hate list will propogate back to cazic from those that &quot;go home&quot;.  (The agro range on these things is extreme, most of the time if you can see it, it is already planning to kill you.)  When another creature enters this agro range, it gets a copy of the original's hate list.  That means that a successful FD will result with Cazic DT the puller in about 60 to 90 seconds.  An experenced puller can over come this quite easily by knowing how to pull, but the more inexperenced the puller - the more likely you will be doing a corpse recovery.<br>
<br>
The most common method to pulling is the pull and pick strategy.  This is where a tank with the highest magic resistances goes out and pulls one or more creatures.  (This tank is usually a hybrid - all 3 have specific talents that make this work well).  The strategy is to kite as few as possible in wide circles and allow another tank to pick one mob at a time.  With this strategy it is very possible to have some extremely bored enchanters in fear because you can pull almost the entire zone one mob at a time.  (Having 2 pickers and 2 pullers will REALLY speed up the rate in which you kill mobs... often faster than your casters can keep up.)  A mage with Call of Hero is extremely useful in this strategy.  If cazic is up it is important to not loose any of the mobs - which can happen due to horrible pathing in the graveyard.<br>
<br>
Another much more ambitious strategy is to divide your group into 2 or more sub groups.  This allows 2 creatures to be killed simultanously.  It is even possible to subdivide until you get to each group killing one mob, but usually pullers cannot bring them in that fast.  This isnt a good idea until you know the zone well.<br>
<br>
As a general rule, listen to the person in chanrge of the raid.  Don't camp until he or she tells you to but when he does don't wait to make sure others do as well.  Tanks should defend the clerics as they camp.  The only bad deaths in the planes are those of the clerics and enchanters.  If the enchanters are not alive then you will be camping and if the clerics are dead then so is everyone else. <br>
<br>
Don't argue about loot.  At the beginning of the raid the rules of looting should be established.  The don't change no matter how much someone wants a rare item.  The planes are about getting loot, but if that all you think about you will hate them.<br>
<br>
Don't wander away, and always use /assist.  Pet owners must keep an eye on their pets at all times, as many an enchanter will die from a pet doing its own thing.  A dead enchanter means a dead group.<br>
<br>
